<paragraph id="8BAD36E2FFBFFF9AE1FF268EBB42FAF3" blockId="19.[151,736,1236,1295]" box="[151,319,1270,1295]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
(
<figureCitation id="13292A67FFBFFF9AE1F7268EBA99FAF3" box="[159,228,1270,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[201,1375,207,1429]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1478]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia rebeli cuprea Penz &amp; Casagrande, new ssp.: a, male holotype Brazil, Amazonas, Borba (DZUP), note that dorsal anterior hairpencil has been removed from the left HW but that of the right HW can be seen in Fig. 10 j; b, female paratype, Brazil, Amazonas, Borba (DZUP); c, male paratype, Brazil, Tapajós, Monte Christo (CMNH). Bia rebeli tapajos Penz &amp; Simonsen, new ssp.: d, male holotype, Brazil, Pará, Belterra, Flona Tapajós (DZUP); e, male paratype, Brazil, Pará, Santarém (CMNH); f, female, Brazil, Tocantins, Ilha do Bananal (DZUP)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569737/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 7</figureCitation>
